---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Wix vs Squarespace 2025: Which Website Builder?',
  description: 'Wix: Drag-and-drop flexibility, 900+ templates, app marketplace. Squarespace: Designer templates, all-in-one platform, better blogging. Choose Wix for customization freedom. Squarespace for design quality and ease.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Wix vs Squarespace', 'website builder comparison', 'Wix review', 'Squarespace review', 'no-code'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0C6EFC]/5 to-[#0052CC]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0C6EFC] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Comparison · 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Wix vs Squarespace
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Wix and Squarespace are the two biggest names in DIY website building. Both have dragged website creation from developers to normal people. Wix offers more freedom. Squarespace offers better design out of the box. Both work. Neither is universally better.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Wix if you want maximum flexibility and don't mind tinkering. Choose Squarespace if you want beautiful design faster and prefer a simpler experience. Wix has more features but can feel cluttered. Squarespace is more opinionated but polished.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Wix</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Squarespace</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of Use</td>
            <td class="p-14">Easy but cluttered</td>
            <td class="p-14">Easy and clean</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Templates</td>
            <td class="p-14">900+ options</td>
            <td class="p-14">150+ designer templates</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Customization</td>
            <td class="p-14">Drag-and-drop freedom</td>
            <td class="p-14">Structured sections</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">E-commerce</td>
            <td class="p-14">Powerful with apps</td>
            <td class="p-14">Built-in and powerful</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Blogging</td>
            <td class="p-14">Basic but functional</td>
            <td class="p-14">Native and excellent</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">App Market</td>
            <td class="p-14">Extensive (500+ apps)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Limited extensions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design Quality</td>
            <td class="p-14">Variable (template dependent)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Consistently high</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Learning Curve</td>
            <td class="p-14">Low to moderate</td>
            <td class="p-14">Low</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best For</td>
            <td class="p-14">Maximum flexibility</td>
            <td class="p-14">Design and simplicity</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wix Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Wix Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Drag-and-Drop Freedom</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix editor gives you true drag-and-drop. Place anything anywhere. No structural constraints. Pixel-perfect control if you want it.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You can build exactly what you envision. No fighting template limitations. Great for people who want specific layouts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Massive Template Library</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Over 900 templates across every industry. More options than any competitor. You'll find something close to what you want.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Starting point matters. More templates means better starting point. Less customization needed from scratch.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">App Market Ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">500+ apps extend functionality. Booking, events, memberships, forums - add almost anything through the app market.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Your site can grow without switching platforms. Need a feature? There's probably an app for that.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Wix ADI (Artificial Design Intelligence)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI builds your site automatically. Answer questions, get a custom site. Faster than starting from scratch.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Quick start for beginners. AI handles initial setup, you customize from there.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">E-commerce Power</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix Stores is a full e-commerce platform. Inventory, payments, shipping - everything included. App ecosystem extends further.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Online stores work out of the box. Scale from small shop to serious business.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Squarespace Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Squarespace Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Consistently Beautiful Design</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Templates are designed by professionals. Everything looks good out of the box. Hard to make something ugly.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Design quality matters. Most people aren't designers. Squarespace compensates with professional templates.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Structured Editor</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Section-based editing keeps things organized. Less freedom than Wix but more guidance. Harder to break the design.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You can't mess it up easily. The structure keeps your site looking professional even if you're not design-savvy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Excellent Blogging Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Blogging is native and mature. Categories, tags, comments - everything works. Content-focused sites shine here.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If content marketing is your strategy, Squarespace is purpose-built for it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Built-in E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace Commerce is powerful. Online stores work beautifully. No apps needed for basic e-commerce functionality.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Sell products without complexity. Everything integrates seamlessly. Design remains consistent across store.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Simpler All-In-One Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Everything you need is included. Hosting, domain, SSL, analytics. No app marketplace complexity. It just works.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Less decision fatigue. Fewer moving parts. Easier to maintain long-term.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Wix Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Free:</strong> Wix branding, limited features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Combo ($16/month):</strong> Remove branding, custom domain</li>
          <li>• <strong>Unlimited ($22/month):</strong> Multiple sites, more storage</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business ($32/month):</strong> E-commerce features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business VIP ($45/month):</strong> Priority support, more features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Hosting included:</strong> All plans include hosting and SSL.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Squarespace Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>No free tier:</strong> 14-day free trial only</li>
          <li>• <strong>Personal ($16/month):</strong> Basic website features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business ($23/month):</strong> Marketing features, analytics</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce ($27/month):</strong> Full e-commerce functionality</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Plus ($49/month):</strong> Advanced e-commerce features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Hosting included:</strong> All plans include hosting and SSL.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Wix If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You want maximum flexibility:</strong> Drag-and-drop freedom matters</li>
          <li>• <strong>You like tinkering:</strong> Enjoy customizing every detail</li>
          <li>• <strong>You need specific features:</strong> App marketplace ecosystem</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want more template options:</strong> 900+ to choose from</li>
          <li>• <strong>You don't mind clutter:</strong> More features means more complexity</li>
          <li>• <strong>Building complex sites:</strong> Membership sites, forums, advanced features</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Squarespace If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You want beautiful design fast:</strong> Professional templates out of the box</li>
          <li>• <strong>You prefer simplicity:</strong> Cleaner interface, fewer options</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're blogging seriously:</strong> Native blogging platform</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want e-commerce simplicity:</strong> Built-in, no apps needed</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're design-challenged:</strong> Hard to make something ugly</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want all-in-one:</strong> Everything included, no app marketplace</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Wix and Squarespace both work. The choice depends on your priorities. Wix offers more freedom. Squarespace offers better design. Wix has more features. Squarespace is simpler.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Wix for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Maximum customization flexibility</li>
        <li>• App marketplace ecosystem</li>
        <li>• Complex feature requirements</li>
        <li>• More template variety</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Squarespace for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Beautiful design with less effort</li>
        <li>• Simpler, cleaner interface</li>
        <li>• Native blogging platform</li>
        <li>• All-in-one simplicity</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't decide?</strong> Start with Squarespace's 14-day free trial. If it feels too limiting, try Wix. Both offer trials. Test both and see which interface you prefer.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-vs-squarespace" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Squarespace</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Modern vs established builders</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code vs open source</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
